article.headline: St. Francis (NY) beats Mount St. Vincent 69-51
article.linkText: St. Francis (NY) beats Mount St. Vincent 69-51
article.story: NEW YORK -- Yunus Hopkinson scored career highs with 28 points and 10 rebounds for his first double-double and St. Francis (NY) pulled away in the second half to beat Division III Mount St. Vincent 69-51 on Wednesday night. Glenn Bracia collected his 100th win as St. Francis' coach, his seventh season at the helm. Leading 25-24 at halftime, St. Francis pulled ahead 44-39 early in the second half after Hopkinson hit a 3-pointer, three free throws and a jumper. Freshman Rasheem Dunn's layup with 3:08 left gave the Terriers a 17-point lead that was never threatened. Dunn scored 13 points, freshman Robert Montgomery scored 10 points and grabbed 12 rebounds, and Glenn Sanabria added 10 points. The Terriers (2-7) made 28 of 42 free throws and outrebounded the Dolphins 63-35. Andrew Curiel scored 12 points and had 12 rebounds for the Dolphins (1-4).
